<SLUG> BC-Cox-AIRPORT-STATS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;    
 &HT;    A STATISTICAL PORTRAIT OF THE NEW HONG KONG AIRPORT
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Eds: Sidebar for Cox-Hong_Kong-Airports
 &HT;    c.1998 Cox News Service (at)
<TEXT>
<P>
   HONG KONG _ Here is a profile of the new Hong Kong International
Airport:
</P>
<P>
   Airport site - 3,083 acres
</P>
<P>
   Passenger capacity - 35 million/year now, eventually 89 million
</P>
<P>
   Cargo capacity - 3 million tons/year now, eventually 9 million
tons
</P>
<P>
   Runways - 1 now, a second by late 1998
</P>
<P>
   Runway length - 12,471 feet.
</P>
<P>
   Passenger Terminal area - 554,000 square feet
</P>
<P>
   Check-in Counters - 288
</P>
<P>
   Parking spaces - 3,100
</P>
<P>
   Waiting lounge seats - 12,530
</P>
<P>
   Source: hkairport.com, the airport's official website.
</P>
<P>
   ENDIT &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
