<P>
   &UR; FOUR GENERATIONS AT THE MOVIES &LR;
</P>
<P>
   At Tuesday night's preview festivities (benefiting the Giants
Community Fund and the ALS Association) for the AMC 1000 Van Ness
theater complex,  &UR; John Field &LR; 's pleasure was both professional and
personal.
</P>
<P>
   Field, a partner in Field Paoli, was chief architect for the
project, which combines movies, restaurants, a gym and
condominiums. His son,  &UR; Matt Field &LR; , put together the deal that
converted the old car showroom into the entertainment/living
complex.
</P>
<P>
   Before them,  &UR; John Field &LR; 's father had run a chain of movie
theaters in Iowa and Minnesota. Architect Field's brother owned
some of the first multiplexes in the country, in Washington, D.C.
</P>
<P>
   And in the early '20s, in the first layer of this
four-generation family sandwich, John Field's grandfather opened
his first theater in downtown Minneapolis, in a storefront with
folding chairs.
</P>
<P>
   _ Dollywood, the  &UR; Dolly Parton &LR; -themed amusement park that is
Tennessee's second top tourist attraction (just after the Great
Smoky Mountains National Park), has announced plans for a new
roller coaster and gospel museum (separate installations). The
roller coaster will include a ``double butterfly loop'' that the
singer says has been designed in homage to her figure.
</P>
