<HEADLINE>
 
</HEADLINE>
  
 (For use by clients of the New York Times News Service)  
 
 Tall Texan's Big Words   By Jon Swartz  
 c.1998 San Francisco Chronicle  
 
Silicon Valley entrepreneur Jim Clark has as many opinions about
the high-tech industry as he has startup ideas. A sampling of his
views:
<TEXT>
<P>
   _ &UR; On former Silicon Graphics Inc. CEO Ed McCracken: &LR;  ``He's a
Napoleon, a classic example of a massive egomaniac. Ed assumed he
was the reason for the company's success, but I fully blame the
current state of SGI on him.''
</P>
<P>
   _ &UR; On Microsoft CEO Bill Gates: &LR;  ``A whole library can be written
about Bill Gates' business practices, but it can be distilled in
one sentence: He's a thief.''
</P>
<P>
   (A Microsoft spokeswoman responded: ``It is too bad that the
leader of a fine company would take business issues and make them
so personal.'')
</P>
<P>
   _ &UR; On Netscape Communications CEO Jim Barksdale: &LR;  ``Jim is like a
Confederate general. There's not too much idle talk, but the man is
a natural leader.''
</P>
<P>
   _ &UR; On At Home CEO and former SGI executive Tom Jermoluk: &LR; 
``Outgoing, gregarious, smart. He was the reason behind a lot of
SGI's success, not Ed McCracken.''
</P>
<P>
   _ &UR; On building a successful startup.  &LR; ``You can't be too
religious or wedded to your ideas. You have to adapt to keep
customers.''
</P>
<P>
   _ &UR; On the Web-browser war. &LR;  ``If Microsoft beats Netscape, the
Internet will be dominated and governed by Microsoft. There will be
no stopping them.''
</P>
<P>
   _ &UR; On mixing politics and high tech: &LR;  ``A waste of time. I don't
have the patience. It's hard to make things happen. I remember
testifying before the Senate in the late 1980s and being asked by
(then Senator Al Gore) and others about what we could do to start
an information superhighway. I told them it already exists. They
just needed to pave it.''
</P>
<P>
   _ &UR; On the Internet. &LR;  ``It has become the standard form of
communication for every (computer) network in the world. The Net is
a massive revolution that has just begun.''
</P>
<P>
   _ &UR; On Microsoft's Windows operating system. &LR;  ``I don't use
Windows, so I got that much going for me.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
