<P>
   ASIA-TRAVEL _ WASHINGTON _ Once an out-of-reach destination for
frugal travelers, east Asia is now more accessible than ever.
Tumbling currencies due to Asia's economic woes have resulted in
deep discounts on airfares, hotel rooms and package tours. With
intra-Asian travel at a near halt, airlines and tour operators are
looking to fill up empty seats and hotel rooms with Western
travelers. Once in Asia, Americans will find their dollar stretch
with drastically-reduced merchandise. (Abulhassan, Cox News
Service.) MOVED.
