<P>
   MEXICO-TURTLES _ XCACEL, Mexico _ Biologists camp on the beach
at Mexico's beautiful Quintana Roo coastline _ called Xcacel and
considered one of most important turtle nesting grounds in the
Caribbean _ to protect endangered turtles and their eggs from
poachers. But soon, they fear, their work will be obliterated. The
state government has quietly sold much of Xcacel to resort hotel
developers, despite a covenant that was signed to protect it and
years of effort to have it declared a federal reserve. Soon, the
turtles could be greeted by as many as 1,500 hotel rooms jammed
onto the small beach, producing glaring lights that would drive the
turtles away. (Ferriss, Cox News Service). MOVED. WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   BAHRAIN-DEMOCRACY _ MANAMA, Bahrain _ Bahrain has everything
American _ Penneys, Dairy Queen and a huge American naval base.
But, it doesn't have democracy. Human rights groups report that the
government regularly uses torture and imprisonment without trial.
The country's leading religious figure is a political prisoner. We
talk to his wife and son. It's as hard to find people who will talk
to reporters in Bahrain as it is in Baghdad. (Kaplow, Cox News
Service). MOVED. WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
