<HEADLINE>
ABOARD THE GOOD SHIP GRIFF
</HEADLINE>
  
 (Eds: This story also moved in the ``l'' lifestyle file)  
 By LEAH GARCHIK  
 c.1998 San Francisco Chronicle
<TEXT>
<P>
   Presenting the key to San Francisco to almost-homeboy  &UR; Merv &LR; 
 &UR; Griffin &LR;  on Tuesday night, Mayor  &UR; Willie Brown &LR;  boasted of the
accomplishments of his administration: The crummy paper key that
used to be presented by everyday mayors has been replaced with a
classy brass replica of the key to Mission Dolores.
</P>
<P>
   The backdrop for this grand event was Griffin's yacht, the Griff
_ available for rent, according to a brochure onboard _ which had
sailed through the Panama Canal from Fort Lauderdale on its first
trip to California. Griffin himself had flown up earlier in the day
from the Southland. ``I don't ride for long periods on the boat,''
said Griffin. ``I have a plane.''
</P>
<P>
   The horde of reporters and cameramen was augmented by several
old friends, including  &UR; Ann Caen &LR; ,  &UR; Wilkes Bashford  &LR; (who said he
thought shawl-collared Griff sweaters might be better than the
current V-necked Griff sweaters) and bassist  &UR; Vernon Alley &LR; , who
said it was a good thing that Griffin had turned out to be so smart
at business, ``because he wasn't going to make it as a singer or a
piano player.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FLASH &LR;
</P>
<P>
   _ A spokeswoman for  &UR; Woody Allen  &LR; said he was upset that he had
to learn about the death of  &UR; Maureen O'Sullivan &LR; ,  &UR; Mia &LR; 
 &UR; Farrow &LR; 's mother, from a newspaper account.
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Nat Freedberg &LR; , who calls himself Lord Bendover as lead
singer for the rock br &LR; and Upper Crust, told Musician magazine what
he's hoping to give fans who attend concerts: ``I'd like them to
come away with venereal disease and ringing in their ears.''
</P>
<P>
   _ Having read that the number of new syphilis cases has been
plummeting in California, &UR; Rich G. &LR;  wonders if the trend indicates
the decline of Western syphilisation? (Further on in the
illustrated exhibit on the workings of Rich G.'s brain, his
suggested Beatles animal songs include &LR;  ``Cat Buy Me Love,'' ``Baby
You Can Drive Macaw,'' ``The Mad-Jackal Mystery Tour'' and
``Something in the Way She Moose.''
</P>
<P>
   _ Cross-pollination in independent bookstores:  &UR; Fran Johns &LR; 
sends word that  &UR; Carrie Theiderman &LR; , manager of A Clean
Well-Lighted Place for Books in San Francisco, is married to
 &UR; Kevin Ryan &LR; , manager of Green Apple Books, and they're expecting a
baby in early August.
</P>
<P>
   _ Looking for a challenge? Side-by-side ads in the latest issue
of the Economist indicate that the International Centre for
Diarrhoeal Disease Research is looking for a director. The job
comes with a car and the opportunity to move to Bangladesh. And the
United Nations is seeking a director-level gender adviser _ able to
``formulate monitoring mechanisms for gender in selected assistance
sectors'' _ in Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; LAW AND ORDER &LR;
</P>
<P>
   The Tampa Tribune reports that a 38-year-old man has filed suit
against the Diamond Dolls Club for injuries, including whiplash,
that he claims to have suffered when a topless dancer hit him in
the head with her breasts.
</P>
<P>
   And in New York, where 20,000 construction workers rallied on
Tuesday to protest the city's use of a nonunion contractor, one
demonstrator was arrested for allegedly assaulting a police horse.
</P>
<P>
   Finally, lawyers for  &UR; Calvin Klein &LR;  have filed papers in federal
court against  &UR; Ralph Lauren &LR; , alleging that the packaging for
Lauren's new scent, Romance, is mighty like the packaging for
Klein's old scent, Eternity. Lauren's company says it is not.
</P>
<P>
   Klein's lawyers say this would be confusing to shoppers.
Lauren's company says it would not.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; TRANSPORTATION ISSUES &LR;
</P>
<P>
   _ The passengers were taking it quite well the other day when a
Muni Metro car got stuck between Church and Castro streets, until
20 minutes into the wait, when the loudspeaker explanation was
broadcast: ``There is a delay in the Muni system.'' After that,
reports a spy  &LR; the passengers weren't taking it so well.
</P>
<P>
   _ The average American walks an average of 1.4 miles a week,
barely 350 yards a day, says ``A Walk in the Woods'' author  &UR; Bill &LR; 
 &UR; Bryson &LR; , who is quoted in the Men's Journal.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WHO SAID WHAT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ``The show is stupid. I know that. But it's OK, one hour a day,
to be that way.''
</P>
<P>
   _ Jerry Springer, announcing that he has signed a seven-figure
contract with St. Martin's Press for ``Ringmaster,'' a
behind-the-scenes glimpse of his show. Springer was quoted in the
New York Daily News.
</P>
