<P>
   BOX-OFFICE (Los Angeles)_ The summer's most expensive movie,
``Armageddon,'' failed to meet blockbuster expectations, but still
dominated the Fourth of July weekend with $52.5 million over its
five-day opening run. By Dave McNary. (Will move in the ``a''
national and ``n'' California news files.)
</P>
<P>
   POLITICS-2001 (Los Angeles) _ As charter reform, term limits and
efforts to break up the city dominate the landscape, Los Angeles
politicians are already positioning themselves for the 2001
campaigns, when such issues will come to a head. By Rick Orlov.
(Will move in the ``a'' national and ``n'' California news files.)
</P>
<P>
   DWARFS-CONVENTION (Los Angeles) _ The annual Little People of
America conference kicked off with a beach party attended by some
150 dwarfs, and continues through the week around the city. By Lee
Condon. (Will move in the ``a'' national and ``n'' California news
files.)
</P>
