u s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-ALLSTAR-NOTEBOOK-COX     07-05 0513
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-ALLSTAR-NOTEBOOK-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Sore shoulder sidelines Sosa
 &HT;    By I. J. Rosenberg
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   DENVER _ The All-Star Game home run derby took another power
blow Sunday when Cubs outfielder Sammy Sosa said he would not be
able to participate because of a sore left shoulder.
</P>
<P>
   Sosa, who has 33 homers and hit a record 20 in June, will also
missed Tuesday's game. He has been replaced on the roster by Reds
second baseman Brett Boone. The Cubs will not have a representative
on the active roster though Sosa will be dressing out. ``The doctor
said three to four days. I can't swing the bat,'' said Sosa, who
missed Sunday's game.
</P>
<P>
   Why Boone?
</P>
<P>
   Every team has to have a representative and the Red traded away
theirs on Saturday, sending reliever Jeff Shaw to the Dodgers.
Boone certainly is hitting .287 with 11 homers and 55 RBIs.
</P>
<P>
   The loss of Sosa leaves the home run derby without another big
bat, Already, Seattle's Ken Griffey Jr. has said he will not
participate along with Rangers outfielder Juan Gonzalez, the major
league RBI leader, and San Diego's Greg Vaughn.
</P>
<P>
   Those that have said they will be in the contest are Mark
McGwire of the Cardinals, Colorado's Vinny Castilla and Braves
third baseman Chipper Jones for the National League and Seattle's
Alex Rodriguez, Baltimore's Rafael Palmeiro, Cleveland's Jim Thome
and Detroit's Damon Easley for the AL. But each team must have five
hitters and right now Braves first baseman Andres Galarraga is not
sure if he will participate. One possibility for the NL is Braves
catcher Javier Lopez while Anaheim's Darin Erstad may suit up for
the AL. Indians shortstop Omar Vizquel, the only All-Star without a
homers, said he would be glad to fill in, adding, ``If they ask me,
I'll do it. In Colorado, everyone has a shot.''
</P>
<P>
   Around with the stars
</P>
<P>
   It hasn't been announced yet by NL manager Jim Leyland but he is
expected to start Braves righthander Greg Maddux Tuesday night. He
will likely face David Wells from the Yankees. ... There will be a
new event in the home run derby with four teams each made up with a
celebrity, major league rookie and retired All-Star. Those expected
to be participating will be actor Kevin Costner, Broncos
quarterback John Elway, Dave Kingman and George Brett. ... Former
Mets star Keith Hernandez was spotted a local bar here over the
weekend and when asked what is it like being on Seinfeld in bed
with Elaine, he said, ``Ultimate professionals, those
Seinfeldians.'' ... Before taking batting practice this afternoon,
many of the All-Stars will play golf this morning at Castle Pines,
where the PGA will hold an even in August. ... Colorado's Castilla
and Ivan Rodriguez of the Rangers will duel each in a video
baseball showdown today. ... Some of the hottest memorabilia at the
FanFest has the name McGwire on it. Said one sports collector shop
owner from St. Louis: ``Everybody wants a McGwire. But the stuff is
just not out there. It's impossible.''
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
