<HEADLINE>
TRAVEL INSURANCE COULD WELL BE WASTE OF CASH 
</HEADLINE>
   By AMY DOAN  
 c.1998 San Francisco Chronicle  
Packing up for summer vacation? If you're planning to buy travel
insurance, you might be wasting your money, according to the
Independent Insurance Agents of America. Supplemental medical
coverage, flight insurance and rental car insurance often duplicate
coverage that you already have in standard homeowners, auto and
life insurance. For more information, go to www.iiaa.org or call
(800) 221-7917.
<TEXT>
<P>
   T-BILLS ONLINE: Starting this month, you can manage your
investments in Treasury bills, notes and bonds via the Web. Check
out www.publicdebt.treas.gov, the site for Treasury Direct
Electronic Services, the government's bookkeeping system for
Treasury auctions. You now can reinvest, check account balances and
request account statements and 1099-INT tax forms online.
</P>
<P>
   ECON 101: Stein Roe &AMP; Farnham has a new pamphlet titled,
``Understanding Economic Indicators.'' The booklet offers a general
brush-up on things like inflation, interest rates and economic
growth. You can obtain a copy by calling (800) 338-2550 or by going
to www.steinroe.com and clicking on ``Investment Center'' and then
``Library.''
</P>
<P>
   LONG-TERM CARE: The California Public Employees' Retirement
System (CalPERS) has extended the 1998 application period for its
long-term care insurance an extra month to July 31. Employees and
retirees of any public agency in California are eligible. You can
request an application form by calling (800) 338-2244 or by
downloading it off www.calpers.ca.gov//ltc.
</P>
<P>
   Chronicle staff writer Amy Doan can be reached by calling (415)
536-5134 or sending an e-mail to doana &LR; sfgate.com.  &LR;
</P>
</TEXT>
