   (NYT3) NEW YORK -- July 5, 1998 -- RADIO-SPORTSBABE-MEDIA, 7-5
-- Nanci Donnellan, the self-described 'Fabulous Sports Babe,' on
the air, left, and with her personalized bus. Knowledgeable and
often irreverent, she is the only female host of a nationally
syndicated sports talk show. About 250,000 sports fans each month
call the Babe's 10 a.m. to 1 p.m. daily call-in show, transmitted
live from New York to 187 stations. It is one of the few radio
programs to generate nearly $1 million in annual revenue. (Marilynn
K.Yee/New York Times Photos)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT2) TUKWILA, Wash. -- July 5, 1998 -- KINKO-PEOPLE-2, 7-5 --
Kinko's outlets, like this one in Tukwila, offer business travelers
and customers with home offices a mix of fax machines, color
printers and networks of computers equipped with popular software
programs and high-speed Internet connections. As millions more
people join the work-at-home trend each year, Kinko's appears to be
doing what people envisioned cybercafes would do - offer an escape
from the isolation that this abundance of modern technology seems
to have created. (Dan Lamont/New York Times Photo)
