<SLUG> BC-NY-SHOOTING-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
GUNMAN WOUNDS 4 IN NEIGHBORING YARDS 
</HEADLINE>
  (mk) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ A gunman on a bicycle rode up to a barbecue in
Brooklyn early Sunday morning and opened fire, striking a
16-year-old who was apparently his intended target, but also
shooting three other people who were attending a family reunion in
a neighboring back yard, police said.
</P>
<P>
   The shootings occurred just before 1 a.m. Sunday in the back
yard of 1 Miami Court in Prospect Heights, said Officer Leslie
Cardona, a police spokeswoman.
</P>
<P>
   The gunman, who is still being sought, pedaled over and began
shooting at the 16-year-old. The youth, who was not identified, was
struck in the hip and taken to Kings County Hospital Center, where
he was in critical but stable condition, police said.
</P>
<P>
   Several stray bullets hit a family having a reunion in a
neighboring yard about 100 yards away, Cardona said. An 11-year-old
girl, who was not identified, was shot in the leg; Aubry Gonsalves,
64, was struck in the neck, and Ann Gonsalves, 39, had a bullet
graze her elbow, police said.
</P>
<P>
   The reunion had brought members of the Gonsalves family together
from New Jersey and as far away as Texas and Florida. By Sunday
afternoon, the Gonsalveses were released from the hospital, and the
11-year-old was upgraded to stable condition, police said.
</P>
<P>
   ``We're just thankful it looks like everyone's going to be all
right,'' said a family member, Dawn Gonsalves.
</P>
</TEXT>
